    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "so u think the nonviolent stuff was \"proven\" to be better because it worked for laws, but what about things like systemic issues or economic stuff? it feels like people still argue about whether the movement actually fixed the core problems or if it just changed the laws without really fixing the actual situation. do you think it was a complete success or just a partial one?",
